         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne, ¶ 2/3/75 ¶  ¶ In working on Chaetospora to day, dear Mr Abbott, I have found that Dr. Hookers name of Chaetospora capillacea will have to be changed, in as much as a good species from South...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">75.03.02</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Francis Abbott</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RAS/B.13 (11), Royal Society of Tasmania Archives, Hobart.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">2/3/75</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In working on Chaetospora to day, dear Mr Abbott, I have found that Dr. Hookers name of <name key="Chaetospora%20capillacea">Chaetospora capillacea</name> will have to be changed, in as much as a good species from South Africa received precisely that name by Nees von Esenbeck long before Dr. Hooker published his Tasmanian species.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Nees von Esenbeck (1836), p. 192; J. Hooker (1860), vol 2, pp. 81-2. </p>
               </note> The name of the latter I propose to change in <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Chaetospora</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">capillaris</hi>
               </seg>, and I should feel obliged, if you will make the necessary alteration in the Census<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B75.13.10, p. 93.</p>
               </note> list with the following quotation <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">F.M.fragm.</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">IX,</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">30</hi>
               </seg>.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B75.03.01, p. 34, not p. 30 as M stated.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd.von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Chaetospora%20capillacea">Chaetospora capillacea</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Chaetospora%20capillaris">Chaetospora capillaris</name>
            </p>
